00:08:24,589 --> 00:08:26,257
Well, I got news
for you, William.

246
00:08:26,340 --> 00:08:29,343
To a jury,
that's gonna sound
like you're full of shit.

247
00:08:29,677 --> 00:08:31,095
Okay, smart guy.

248
00:08:31,429 --> 00:08:32,847
Pick up that journal.

249
00:08:33,556 --> 00:08:34,765
Give me a stock.

250
00:08:34,849 --> 00:08:36,225
NASDAQ, New York
Stock Exchange.

251
00:08:36,309 --> 00:08:38,144
I don't give a shit.
Just pick one.

252
00:08:39,145 --> 00:08:40,938
All right, Computech.
Computech.

253
00:08:41,022 --> 00:08:43,191
One point five nine
billion shares
outstanding.

254
00:08:43,274 --> 00:08:45,193
Yesterday's close,
32 flat.

255
00:08:45,276 --> 00:08:47,111
Today's opening,
33 and a quarter.

256
00:08:47,195 --> 00:08:48,404
PE's at 17.

257
00:08:48,487 --> 00:08:50,698
Earnings expected
to grow at 2% a year.

258
00:08:50,781 --> 00:08:51,866
What it doesn't
say in there

259
00:08:51,949 --> 00:08:53,326
is that the earnings
aren't gonna grow,

260
00:08:53,409 --> 00:08:54,994
because their CEO
doesn't give a shit.

261
00:08:55,077 --> 00:08:57,580
Which makes it a value trap
dressed up like a princess

262
00:08:57,663 --> 00:08:59,874
and I wouldn't touch it
with a 10-foot pole.

263
00:08:59,957 --> 00:09:01,209
That's a pretty
neat trick, William.

264
00:09:01,292 --> 00:09:03,336
But it isn't gonna
stop this subpoena.

265
00:09:03,544 --> 00:09:05,713
It's not a trick.
It's what I do.

266
00:09:06,631 --> 00:09:07,715
And what you're
gonna do

267
00:09:07,798 --> 00:09:08,799
is stop that
son of a bitch

268
00:09:08,883 --> 00:09:10,843
from getting his hands
on my program.

269
00:09:16,224 --> 00:09:18,935
Rachel, whatever it is,
it's going to have
to wait.

270
00:09:19,352 --> 00:09:21,103
Okay, but you told me
to bring you
everything I have

271
00:09:21,187 --> 00:09:22,313
on the Bailey case
this morning.

272
00:09:22,396 --> 00:09:23,522
Great. Leave it
on my desk,

273
00:09:23,606 --> 00:09:25,274
and I'll get to it
sometime this week.

274
00:09:25,358 --> 00:09:26,400
Oh, I'm sorry,
Jessica.

275
00:09:26,484 --> 00:09:28,027
I was really hoping
that we could
go over it today.

276
00:09:28,110 --> 00:09:29,445
I was hoping to be
out the door by now.

277
00:09:29,528 --> 00:09:30,655
Look, I know
that I said

278
00:09:30,738 --> 00:09:32,531
this wouldn't take up
too much
of your time, but...

279
00:09:32,615 --> 00:09:35,201
Rachel, I said
I would do this
and I will,

280
00:09:35,701 --> 00:09:37,286
but you just
have to be patient.

281
00:09:37,370 --> 00:09:38,496
I understand.

282
00:09:38,579 --> 00:09:40,831
It's just, Leonard Bailey's
been patient for 12 years.

283
00:09:40,915 --> 00:09:42,625
And I have sympathy
for the man,

284
00:09:43,376 --> 00:09:44,835
but today's not the day.

285
00:09:53,844 --> 00:09:54,887
Don't bother
with another menu.

286
00:09:54,971 --> 00:09:56,639
I'll just have
the Cobb salad.

287
00:09:58,641 --> 00:09:59,600
What do you think
you're doing?

288
00:09:59,684 --> 00:10:00,768
What does it look like
I'm doing?

289
00:10:01,018 --> 00:10:02,019
I'm having lunch
with a client

290
00:10:02,103 --> 00:10:03,354
to discuss his
investment business.

291
00:10:03,437 --> 00:10:05,439
You don't represent
my investment business.

292
00:10:05,523 --> 00:10:06,691
Which is exactly
why we need
to have lunch.

293
00:10:06,774 --> 00:10:07,900
No, we don't need
to have anything.

294
00:10:07,984 --> 00:10:10,069
Because the deal was
Harvey gets me cleared
of criminal charges,

295
00:10:10,152 --> 00:10:11,612
then you get the rest
of my business.

296
00:10:11,696 --> 00:10:13,030
I don't care what
the deal was, William.

297
00:10:13,114 --> 00:10:14,407
I care
what the deal is.

298
00:10:14,490 --> 00:10:16,075
Because now that that
indictment's come down,

299
00:10:16,158 --> 00:10:19,370
Harvey is going
to be spending
all of his time on you.

300
00:10:19,578 --> 00:10:20,913
That's not my problem.

301
00:10:20,997 --> 00:10:22,957
I'm making it
your problem.

302
00:10:23,040 --> 00:10:25,710
We get all of your business
or we handle none of it.

303
00:10:25,793 --> 00:10:26,877
Bullshit.

304
00:10:26,961 --> 00:10:29,380
You quit, you lose billables
you can't afford to lose.

305
00:10:29,755 --> 00:10:31,549
We quit and it looks
like we realized

306
00:10:31,632 --> 00:10:33,676
your case was a loser
and wanted
distance from it,

307
00:10:33,759 --> 00:10:35,219
which you can't afford.

308
00:10:35,303 --> 00:10:37,555
You really wanna start
a business relationship
this way?

309
00:10:38,472 --> 00:10:40,725
I don't give a shit
how it starts, William.

310
00:10:40,808 --> 00:10:42,143
I give a shit
how it looks.

311
00:10:43,185 --> 00:10:44,186
Oh.

312
00:10:44,270 --> 00:10:46,147
That's why
you did this here.

313
00:10:46,230 --> 00:10:48,733
You want it to look like
you already
represent my firm.

314
00:10:48,816 --> 00:10:50,735
Well, look at that.

315
00:10:51,068 --> 00:10:53,154
Looks like I'm worth
hiring after all.

316
00:10:53,988 --> 00:10:55,948
So, are we actually
going to talk business

317
00:10:56,032 --> 00:10:58,576
or am I just gonna
bill you for the pleasure
of my company?

318
00:11:06,250 --> 00:11:08,210
Mike, what can
I do for you?

319
00:11:10,212 --> 00:11:12,840
You can tell me if you do
straight up therapy or not.

320
00:11:13,257 --> 00:11:14,467
What's on your mind?

321
00:11:14,925 --> 00:11:16,260
You didn't answer
my question.

322
00:11:16,844 --> 00:11:17,845
I didn't think
I needed to,

323
00:11:17,928 --> 00:11:19,472
since we've been doing
straight up therapy

324
00:11:19,555 --> 00:11:20,848
since you got here.

325
00:11:20,931 --> 00:11:23,476
So, you want to tell me
what you're here for?

326
00:11:27,146 --> 00:11:30,983
My parents were killed
by a drunk driver
when I was 11.

327
00:11:31,067 --> 00:11:32,401
And yesterday,
I found out

328
00:11:32,485 --> 00:11:34,695
that Kevin almost killed
someone drunk driving.

329
00:11:34,779 --> 00:11:36,864
So, I need you to help me
act normal around him

330
00:11:36,947 --> 00:11:38,908
so that I can get
what I need
so I can get out of here.

331
00:11:39,116 --> 00:11:41,202
Oh, well, that's gonna
be a problem.

332
00:11:41,285 --> 00:11:42,495
Because
the goal of therapy

333
00:11:42,578 --> 00:11:44,955
is not to act normal,
it's to be normal.

334
00:11:45,039 --> 00:11:46,332
Yeah, well,
I'll be normal

335
00:11:46,415 --> 00:11:47,833
when I'm home
with the woman I love

336
00:11:47,917 --> 00:11:50,419
instead of dreaming
that the guy I'm sharing
a cell with killed her.

337
00:11:50,795 --> 00:11:51,796
What?

338
00:11:51,879 --> 00:11:54,048
I had a dream last night

339
00:11:54,507 --> 00:11:56,967
that I didn't have
to inform
on Kevin anymore

340
00:11:57,051 --> 00:11:59,428
because he killed Rachel
in an accident.

341
00:11:59,804 --> 00:12:01,389
And I must have been
talking about it
in my sleep

342
00:12:01,472 --> 00:12:03,182
because he asked me
about it today.

343
00:12:03,265 --> 00:12:05,184
So, I told him
the accident part

344
00:12:05,267 --> 00:12:06,644
and then
we got in a fight.

345
00:12:06,811 --> 00:12:07,978
A fight about what?

346
00:12:08,062 --> 00:12:10,606
I asked him
if he even felt bad
about the guy he hit.

347
00:12:10,856 --> 00:12:12,483
So, you turned it
back on him.

348
00:12:12,858 --> 00:12:13,984
What is that even
supposed to mean?

349
00:12:14,068 --> 00:12:16,028
It means that
I think you picked
a fight with Kevin

350
00:12:16,112 --> 00:12:18,239
because you didn't
wanna think about why
you had that dream.

351
00:12:18,322 --> 00:12:19,949
I know why
I had that dream.

352
00:12:20,032 --> 00:12:22,868
It's because he almost
killed someone the same way
my parents were killed.

353
00:12:22,952 --> 00:12:24,453
No, you had the dream
because you don't
wanna deal with

354
00:12:24,537 --> 00:12:25,621
what you're doing
to your friend.

355
00:12:25,913 --> 00:12:28,249
Oh, this again.
Yes, this again.

356
00:12:28,916 --> 00:12:31,502
Mike, why do you think
that part of the dream
was finding out

357
00:12:31,585 --> 00:12:33,462
that you didn't have
to inform on him anymore?

358
00:12:33,546 --> 00:12:35,256
God damn it,
I did not come here

359
00:12:35,339 --> 00:12:36,715
to second-guess
my decision.

360
00:12:36,799 --> 00:12:38,509
Do you know what?
I don't care.

361
00:12:38,968 --> 00:12:40,428
Because I wouldn't
be doing my job

362
00:12:40,511 --> 00:12:43,347
if I didn't inform you
that actions
have consequences.

363
00:12:43,431 --> 00:12:44,432
And you seem to think

364
00:12:44,515 --> 00:12:46,392
that the only consequence
of what you're doing

365
00:12:46,475 --> 00:12:48,102
is getting
out of here early,
but it's not.

366
00:12:48,185 --> 00:12:50,688
No. I think
you don't know shit about
what I've been through.

367
00:12:51,522 --> 00:12:53,691
It was a mistake coming
to you for help.

368
00:12:58,070 --> 00:13:00,114
...and this is the
fifth bedroom.

369
00:13:00,197 --> 00:13:02,366
And I'm completely open
to you knocking
down walls

370
00:13:02,450 --> 00:13:03,701
or removing windows,
by the way.

371
00:13:03,784 --> 00:13:05,828
Oh, no,
I love the windows.

372
00:13:05,911 --> 00:13:07,037
They let in
so much light.

373
00:13:07,121 --> 00:13:09,498
I agree, we should add
a wall of glass.
What do you think?

374
00:13:09,582 --> 00:13:11,125
I think the place
is beautiful

375
00:13:11,208 --> 00:13:13,210
and I appreciate
you bringing
these photos over,

376
00:13:13,294 --> 00:13:15,838
but when can we go
see it in person?

377
00:13:17,256 --> 00:13:18,340
Uh, in person?

378
00:13:18,424 --> 00:13:19,467
Yes, of course.

379
00:13:19,550 --> 00:13:21,051
I need to see the space

380
00:13:21,135 --> 00:13:22,470
before I can
start drafting anything.

381
00:13:22,553 --> 00:13:24,138
I was just thinking
we could work
closely together

382
00:13:24,221 --> 00:13:26,182
for the next
60 to 90 days
before you started that.

383
00:13:26,265 --> 00:13:27,349
That wouldn't
be productive.

384
00:13:27,433 --> 00:13:28,809
But I couldn't possibly
make it out there

385
00:13:28,893 --> 00:13:30,186
in less than seven
to 10 business days.

386
00:13:30,269 --> 00:13:31,479
That's too bad.

387
00:13:31,562 --> 00:13:33,230
I was gonna be out there
the day after tomorrow.

388
00:13:33,314 --> 00:13:34,482
I was thinking
we could see the space

389
00:13:34,565 --> 00:13:35,566
and then maybe
go have lunch.

390
00:13:36,066 --> 00:13:37,234
Lunch?

391
00:13:38,402 --> 00:13:39,403
Together?

392
00:13:39,987 --> 00:13:42,781
Well, I wasn't
thinking of eating
in separate restaurants.

393
00:13:43,157 --> 00:13:44,825
(LAUGHS)
Of course you weren't.

394
00:13:44,909 --> 00:13:46,243
The day after tomorrow
is perfect.

395
00:13:46,285 --> 00:13:48,287
But I thought
you couldn't...
I can and I will.

396
00:13:48,370 --> 00:13:49,830
And I will meet you
at my ancestral home

397
00:13:49,914 --> 00:13:52,082
that I have owned
for quite some time,
the day after tomorrow.

398
00:13:59,632 --> 00:14:02,468
Your Honor,
I'm simply requesting
Mr. Sutter hand over...

399
00:14:02,551 --> 00:14:04,094
Something he has
no right to.

400
00:14:04,178 --> 00:14:05,387
I have every right
to make sure that

401
00:14:05,471 --> 00:14:07,264
your client is operating
within the law.

402
00:14:07,348 --> 00:14:10,351
And what exactly
is your basis to say
that he isn't?

403
00:14:10,434 --> 00:14:12,561
Your Honor,
when you break
the home run record

404
00:14:12,645 --> 00:14:14,188
and someone says
your bat is corked,

405
00:14:14,480 --> 00:14:15,981
you turn it over
to show it's not.

406
00:14:16,941 --> 00:14:18,275
Except when that bat
is the reason

407
00:14:18,359 --> 00:14:19,693
you hit
all those homers.

408
00:14:19,777 --> 00:14:21,362
Because the second
he gets it,

409
00:14:21,445 --> 00:14:23,656
everyone in the world
is gonna know
what's in it,

410
00:14:23,739 --> 00:14:24,865
and my client

411
00:14:24,949 --> 00:14:26,992
might as well go out
of business right now.

412
00:14:27,284 --> 00:14:28,786
That is a
ridiculous supposition

413
00:14:28,869 --> 00:14:30,704
without a shred
of proof to back it up.

414
00:14:30,788 --> 00:14:32,206
How's this for proof?

415
00:14:32,289 --> 00:14:33,707
Your Honor,
six years ago,

416
00:14:33,791 --> 00:14:37,002
Mr. Cahill went
on a fishing expedition
just like this one.

417
00:14:37,086 --> 00:14:38,379
That has nothing
to do with this.

418
00:14:38,462 --> 00:14:39,463
Oh, doesn't it?

419
00:14:39,547 --> 00:14:41,632
He subpoenaed
a proprietary
trading program

420
00:14:41,715 --> 00:14:43,300
from Kessler Capital,

421
00:14:43,384 --> 00:14:44,802
it proved no wrong-doing,

422
00:14:44,885 --> 00:14:46,512
and 10 months later,
they were out
of business.

423
00:14:46,595 --> 00:14:48,222
That has nothing to do
with my subpoena.

424
00:14:48,305 --> 00:14:51,392
And I have
an affidavit here
from Mr. Kessler saying

425
00:14:51,475 --> 00:14:53,727
it was directly because
of your subpoena.

426
00:14:53,811 --> 00:14:56,063
Mr. Cahill,
is what he's saying true?

427
00:14:56,355 --> 00:14:58,065
Did you go after Kessler
in the same manner

428
00:14:58,148 --> 00:14:59,650
and did he go under
10 months later?

429
00:15:00,609 --> 00:15:01,986
Yes, but...
No buts.

430
00:15:02,945 --> 00:15:05,614
Do you have
any other evidence
to present to the court?

431
00:15:06,156 --> 00:15:07,491
Not at this time,
Your Honor.

432
00:15:08,033 --> 00:15:09,702
Then your request
is denied.

433
00:15:10,494 --> 00:15:11,662
(GAVEL BANGING)

434
00:15:16,125 --> 00:15:17,418
LOUIS:
Oh, there you are.

435
00:15:17,501 --> 00:15:18,877
What the hell are you doing
in the executive kitchen?

436
00:15:18,961 --> 00:15:20,004
What does it look like
I'm doing?

437
00:15:20,045 --> 00:15:21,922
I'm being executive.
But you're not
an executive.

438
00:15:22,006 --> 00:15:24,341
Until I made
the executive decision
that I was.

439
00:15:25,342 --> 00:15:27,469
Now, is there something
I can help you with?

440
00:15:27,553 --> 00:15:29,430
Yeah, I want you
to forget that latte

441
00:15:29,513 --> 00:15:31,557
and get me
unfettered access
to my new home

442
00:15:31,640 --> 00:15:32,641
after thoroughly
cleansing it

443
00:15:32,725 --> 00:15:34,268
of any trace of its
former occupants.

444
00:15:34,351 --> 00:15:35,936
And why exactly do you
need me to do that?

445
00:15:36,020 --> 00:15:37,396
Because Tara wants
to see the house

446
00:15:37,479 --> 00:15:39,106
and then have
lunch with me
the day after tomorrow.

447
00:15:39,189 --> 00:15:41,275
Louis, your offer
was just accepted

448
00:15:41,358 --> 00:15:43,777
and there's never been
a one-day escrow
in the history of escrows.

449
00:15:43,861 --> 00:15:44,945
You don't think
I know that?

450
00:15:45,029 --> 00:15:46,280
I just spent
the last hour arguing

451
00:15:46,363 --> 00:15:47,573
with five different
escrow officers.

452
00:15:47,656 --> 00:15:48,907
I get it.

453
00:15:49,241 --> 00:15:50,451
You want me
to get people
to do things

454
00:15:50,534 --> 00:15:52,244
they'd never be
willing to do
in a time frame

455
00:15:52,328 --> 00:15:53,829
that makes it impossible
for them to do it in.

456
00:15:53,912 --> 00:15:54,913
Exactly.

457
00:15:54,997 --> 00:15:56,707
Then make me
a double latte and get
the hell out of my way

458
00:15:56,790 --> 00:15:59,918
because I'm about to
executive-decision your
sorry ass into that house.

459
00:16:02,254 --> 00:16:03,881
HARVEY:
What are you drinking?

460
00:16:03,964 --> 00:16:04,965
A 60-year-old bottle

461
00:16:05,049 --> 00:16:06,467
of the finest single malt
in the world.

462
00:16:06,550 --> 00:16:07,593
Then get me a glass.

463
00:16:07,676 --> 00:16:09,637
Not until I know
what happened
in court today.

464
00:16:09,720 --> 00:16:11,013
Well, let me
put it this way.

465
00:16:11,430 --> 00:16:13,849
The only thing that
Sean Cahill's gonna
be drinking tonight

466
00:16:13,932 --> 00:16:15,392
is a shit-out-
of-luck daiquiri.

467
00:16:15,893 --> 00:16:17,102
How did you get it done?

468
00:16:17,186 --> 00:16:20,356
I established a pattern
of him going fishing
without enough bait.

469
00:16:20,439 --> 00:16:21,774
Then have a drink before
you get back in there

470
00:16:21,857 --> 00:16:24,568
and knock the bastard out
before he can throw
another punch.

471
00:16:24,860 --> 00:16:25,819
What are you saying?

472
00:16:25,903 --> 00:16:27,571
I'm saying I want you
to get this
entire action dismissed.

473
00:16:29,698 --> 00:16:31,283
William, that's
a terrible idea.

474
00:16:31,367 --> 00:16:33,410
Not to me,
because he's got nothing.

475
00:16:33,494 --> 00:16:36,080
I don't care,
what you're suggesting
is a mistake.

476
00:16:36,664 --> 00:16:37,998
You still haven't
told me why.

477
00:16:38,082 --> 00:16:39,667
Because you only get
one shot at dismissal

478
00:16:39,750 --> 00:16:41,168
and now's not the time
to take it.

479
00:16:41,251 --> 00:16:43,212
Well, I say it is and
I'm not suggesting it.

480
00:16:43,295 --> 00:16:44,546
I'm flat out
telling you to do it.

481
00:16:44,630 --> 00:16:47,508
I didn't get where I am
by letting my clients
bully me.

482
00:16:47,591 --> 00:16:50,678
And I didn't get where I am
by allowing my employees
to dictate terms.

483
00:16:50,761 --> 00:16:53,013
Which I already did
once today and I'm not
gonna do it again.

484
00:16:53,097 --> 00:16:54,181
What's that
supposed to mean?

485
00:16:54,264 --> 00:16:55,766
It means Jessica Pearson
convinced me

486
00:16:55,849 --> 00:16:58,060
to give your firm
the rest of my business
this afternoon.

487
00:16:58,519 --> 00:17:00,562
So, if you don't move
to have the charges
against me dismissed,

488
00:17:00,646 --> 00:17:02,022
I'll have her
do it for you.

489
00:17:12,491 --> 00:17:13,951
Harvey, I was just
on my way out.

490
00:17:14,034 --> 00:17:15,661
Well, you can be
on your way back in,

491
00:17:15,744 --> 00:17:17,162
because I just came
from Sutter's.

492
00:17:17,246 --> 00:17:19,164
I take it he told you
about our little
conversation today.

493
00:17:19,248 --> 00:17:21,792
If by conversation
you mean going
behind my back

494
00:17:21,875 --> 00:17:23,210
and getting his
investment business,

495
00:17:23,293 --> 00:17:24,670
then yeah, he told me.

496
00:17:24,753 --> 00:17:26,422
I didn't go
behind your back.

497
00:17:26,505 --> 00:17:28,090
I saw an opportunity
and I took it.

498
00:17:28,173 --> 00:17:31,218
Well, now he's seeing
an opportunity
and he's taking it.

499
00:17:31,301 --> 00:17:32,302
What are you
talking about?

500
00:17:32,386 --> 00:17:33,846
He's leveraging
what you did

501
00:17:33,929 --> 00:17:36,140
to get me to move
for an immediate dismissal.

502
00:17:36,974 --> 00:17:38,684
And don't tell me,
you think
it's gonna work.

503
00:17:38,767 --> 00:17:39,852
I sure as hell do.

504
00:17:39,935 --> 00:17:41,145
And the second it does,

505
00:17:41,228 --> 00:17:44,022
Mike's chance at getting out
goes with it, thanks to you.

506
00:17:44,481 --> 00:17:45,774
Hang on there, tiger.

507
00:17:46,608 --> 00:17:48,736
You're not in this position
because of something I did.

508
00:17:48,819 --> 00:17:50,446
You're in it
because of Sutter.

509
00:17:50,529 --> 00:17:52,614
And he'd be
demanding you to have
this case dismissed

510
00:17:52,698 --> 00:17:54,450
whether we have his
other business or not.

511
00:17:54,533 --> 00:17:55,534
Well, that's not
the point.

512
00:17:55,617 --> 00:17:56,952
No, Harvey, the point is

513
00:17:57,035 --> 00:17:58,787
I have been out there
busting my ass

514
00:17:58,871 --> 00:18:01,415
trying to find us
new business for days.

515
00:18:01,498 --> 00:18:02,833
And do you know
what they keep asking?

516
00:18:03,167 --> 00:18:05,210
Why don't we have
Sutter's investment business?

517
00:18:05,294 --> 00:18:06,378
Goddamn right.

518
00:18:06,462 --> 00:18:08,547
We needed it,
I got it,

519
00:18:08,630 --> 00:18:10,466
and now they're not
asking anymore.

520
00:18:11,842 --> 00:18:13,802
What's gonna happen
when we lose this case

521
00:18:13,886 --> 00:18:15,304
and his business goes away?

522
00:18:15,387 --> 00:18:16,555
What happens is

523
00:18:16,638 --> 00:18:18,599
we're already built
back up by then.

524
00:18:18,682 --> 00:18:20,392
So, instead of
blaming me

525
00:18:20,476 --> 00:18:22,186
for the position
Sutter has put you in,

526
00:18:22,269 --> 00:18:25,355
I suggest you go ahead
and find yourself
a way out of it.

527
00:18:31,987 --> 00:18:33,697
Rachel, what can I
do for you?

528
00:18:34,198 --> 00:18:36,784
I was hoping
you could do something
for Leonard Bailey.

529
00:18:36,867 --> 00:18:39,077
I drafted a motion
to reopen his case,

530
00:18:39,161 --> 00:18:41,163
but I need
a current member
of the Bar to file it.

531
00:18:41,246 --> 00:18:43,791
And what happened
to the person you said
was gonna take this on?

532
00:18:43,874 --> 00:18:45,083
She can't get to it
until later this week,

533
00:18:45,167 --> 00:18:46,627
but I want to get on this
as soon as possible.

534
00:18:46,710 --> 00:18:48,128
Rachel, I'm sorry,
but I told you before,

535
00:18:48,212 --> 00:18:50,297
I don't have the resources
to work on this case now...

536
00:18:50,380 --> 00:18:51,590
Professor,
this man has a wife

537
00:18:51,673 --> 00:18:54,468
who gave up on him
and children
that he doesn't see.

538
00:18:55,052 --> 00:18:57,262
His entire life
is passing him by,

539
00:18:57,387 --> 00:18:59,848
and the only way for him
to start getting it back

540
00:18:59,932 --> 00:19:03,227
is to just have someone
who cares enough
about him

541
00:19:03,310 --> 00:19:06,563
that they give him
a half hour
of their time.

542
00:19:08,524 --> 00:19:10,526
Let me see your motion.

543
00:19:18,075 --> 00:19:19,076
(SIGHS)

544
00:19:20,369 --> 00:19:22,371
This is well drafted.
Thank you.

545
00:19:23,080 --> 00:19:25,249
But I'm afraid
it won't work.

546
00:19:26,083 --> 00:19:27,125
No, what are you
talking... No, look.

547
00:19:27,209 --> 00:19:28,585
There's no reason
that he should've
been convicted.

548
00:19:28,669 --> 00:19:30,295
Look at the evidence.
That's not the point.

549
00:19:30,379 --> 00:19:32,589
Rachel, I've worked
on dozens of these cases.

550
00:19:33,131 --> 00:19:34,675
And like it or not,
the standard to reopen

551
00:19:34,758 --> 00:19:36,260
is higher than what
it says in the books.

552
00:19:36,343 --> 00:19:39,263
You need
something undeniable.

553
00:19:39,972 --> 00:19:41,515
Then what am I
supposed to do?

554
00:19:41,598 --> 00:19:44,476
You're supposed
to use your gumption
to find that something

555
00:19:45,102 --> 00:19:47,813
and get Leonard Bailey
the justice
he's been waiting for.

556
00:19:51,900 --> 00:19:54,528
Harvey, it's late.
Whatever you're doing here,

557
00:19:54,611 --> 00:19:55,988
it's gonna have
to wait until morning.

558
00:19:56,071 --> 00:19:57,698
It can't.
Why is that?

559
00:19:57,948 --> 00:19:59,283
Because Sutter
wants me to move

560
00:19:59,366 --> 00:20:01,034
for an
immediate dismissal.
What?

561
00:20:01,577 --> 00:20:03,203
You leveraged me into
bringing this indictment

562
00:20:03,287 --> 00:20:04,371
and now
you want to toss it?

563
00:20:04,454 --> 00:20:05,747
I don't want to toss it.

564
00:20:05,831 --> 00:20:06,832
But if I don't,

565
00:20:06,915 --> 00:20:08,709
he's gonna find
someone else who will.

566
00:20:08,792 --> 00:20:10,377
What are you doing
here, Harvey?

567
00:20:10,460 --> 00:20:12,671
Nothing, I'm just
finishing my dinner.

568
00:20:12,754 --> 00:20:14,548
Thing is,
I don't like to litter.

569
00:20:14,631 --> 00:20:15,883
So, why don't you
do me a favor.

570
00:20:15,966 --> 00:20:18,176
If I forget this
when I go,

571
00:20:20,429 --> 00:20:22,514
why don't you
take it upstairs
and throw it away?

572
00:20:22,598 --> 00:20:23,765
What's in the bag,
Harvey?

573
00:20:24,141 --> 00:20:25,642
A wrapper,

574
00:20:25,726 --> 00:20:28,145
a couple napkins,
and a few extra fries.

575
00:20:28,228 --> 00:20:29,605
What the hell
is in the bag, Harvey?

576
00:20:29,897 --> 00:20:31,481
What you needed to keep
this case going

577
00:20:31,565 --> 00:20:32,983
and I stopped you
from getting.

578
00:20:33,066 --> 00:20:34,401
Damn it, you said
you were gonna defend him

579
00:20:34,484 --> 00:20:35,819
to the best
of your ability.

580
00:20:35,903 --> 00:20:37,696
And I meant it,
but I also knew

581
00:20:37,779 --> 00:20:41,283
if push came to shove,
I'd do what I had to
to get Mike out.

582
00:20:41,366 --> 00:20:42,743
And I made
my peace with it.

583
00:20:42,826 --> 00:20:44,453
Yeah, well, I haven't.
Yes, you have.

584
00:20:44,536 --> 00:20:45,579
What are you
talking about?

585
00:20:45,662 --> 00:20:48,248
You've been giving me
this song and dance

586
00:20:48,332 --> 00:20:51,460
about not colluding
and it didn't matter
what I said back to you

587
00:20:51,543 --> 00:20:53,003
as long as
it was something

588
00:20:53,086 --> 00:20:54,755
to let you believe
we wouldn't.

589
00:20:54,838 --> 00:20:57,674
Because that song
wasn't for me,
it was for you.

590
00:20:57,883 --> 00:20:59,051
Oh, for me?
Bullshit.

591
00:20:59,134 --> 00:21:00,427
I don't think so, Sean.

592
00:21:00,510 --> 00:21:02,095
Because you don't break
a guy out of prison

593
00:21:02,179 --> 00:21:04,181
just to advance
your career.

594
00:21:05,015 --> 00:21:06,975
This means
something to you.

595
00:21:07,893 --> 00:21:08,977
I don't need to know
what it is,

596
00:21:09,061 --> 00:21:10,604
but it means something
to me, too.

597
00:21:10,687 --> 00:21:12,981
So, let's just admit
that we're in this together

598
00:21:13,065 --> 00:21:14,399
and get this thing done.

599
00:21:15,233 --> 00:21:17,611
Take that garbage
and throw it away.

600
00:21:27,371 --> 00:21:28,997
Now can I
have champagne?

601
00:21:30,040 --> 00:21:31,792
You got the realtor
to give you
the key to the house.

602
00:21:31,875 --> 00:21:33,460
Not only that,
I got him to agree

603
00:21:33,543 --> 00:21:34,962
to take the Kellmans
to brunch tomorrow

604
00:21:35,045 --> 00:21:37,464
from 10:00 to 2:00
to celebrate
their big sale.

605
00:21:37,547 --> 00:21:38,507
Well, that is great,
Donna,

606
00:21:38,590 --> 00:21:40,133
but I don't just need
to get into the house,

607
00:21:40,217 --> 00:21:42,135
I need Tara to believe
that it's my house.

608
00:21:42,219 --> 00:21:43,637
Which means...
No lockbox on the door,

609
00:21:43,720 --> 00:21:44,846
no for sale sign
in the yard,

610
00:21:44,930 --> 00:21:46,390
and no personal belongings
in the house.

611
00:21:46,473 --> 00:21:48,684
Which is why we are
gonna be there at 10:01

612
00:21:48,767 --> 00:21:50,477
to stage the shit
out of that place.

613
00:21:50,560 --> 00:21:52,312
Oh, and these are
coming with us.

614
00:21:56,191 --> 00:21:57,859
You reframed pictures
of Bruno.

615
00:21:58,235 --> 00:21:59,861
In the style of the house.

616
00:22:00,278 --> 00:22:01,571
And not just Bruno.

617
00:22:04,616 --> 00:22:05,826
Mikado.
(CHUCKLES)

618
00:22:06,702 --> 00:22:08,078
It's perfect, Donna.

619
00:22:08,704 --> 00:22:10,163
I just thought showing
Tara your wood

620
00:22:10,247 --> 00:22:12,624
wasn't the only way
to show her what
kind of man you are.

621
00:22:13,041 --> 00:22:14,167
Thank you, Donna.

622
00:22:14,543 --> 00:22:15,919
You're welcome, Louis.

623
00:22:19,256 --> 00:22:20,298
(SIGHS)

624
00:22:20,382 --> 00:22:21,633
Since when do
we get a room

625
00:22:21,717 --> 00:22:23,927
instead of having to use
those damn phones?

626
00:22:24,678 --> 00:22:27,180
Since I officially became
part of your legal team.

627
00:22:28,306 --> 00:22:29,683
My legal team?
That's right.

628
00:22:29,766 --> 00:22:32,269
The firm that I work for
is taking your case.

629
00:22:36,481 --> 00:22:37,774
After all this time.

630
00:22:40,444 --> 00:22:41,778
Thank you.

631
00:22:43,405 --> 00:22:44,948
You're welcome.

632
00:22:45,991 --> 00:22:48,201
But we still need to get
the case reopened.

633
00:22:48,285 --> 00:22:51,246
And to do that, we need
to find something new.

634
00:22:51,705 --> 00:22:52,831
So, where do we
get that?

635
00:22:53,123 --> 00:22:54,708
I was going through
the state's case file,

636
00:22:54,791 --> 00:22:56,501
and I read
your police report.

637
00:22:56,585 --> 00:22:58,628
You said there was
a woman with you
that night

638
00:22:58,712 --> 00:23:01,715
who can testify
that you didn't kill
that couple.

639
00:23:01,798 --> 00:23:03,425
That's right. Maria.

640
00:23:03,800 --> 00:23:05,218
But that's not new.

641
00:23:05,635 --> 00:23:07,471
Well, it's new as far as
the court's concerned,

642
00:23:07,554 --> 00:23:09,431
because it was
never admitted at trial.

643
00:23:09,514 --> 00:23:11,391
Well, let's admit it.
It's not that easy.

644
00:23:11,475 --> 00:23:13,226
I need to understand
why it was never admitted.

645
00:23:13,310 --> 00:23:16,813
Because the damn woman
up and disappeared
before my trial.

646
00:23:17,522 --> 00:23:19,191
My lawyer
didn't do a thing.

647
00:23:19,274 --> 00:23:20,817
You had an alibi witness

648
00:23:20,901 --> 00:23:22,569
and your public defender
let her get away?

649
00:23:22,652 --> 00:23:23,820
That's what
I've been saying.

650
00:23:23,904 --> 00:23:26,073
Maria could have
told the jury
that I didn't do it.

651
00:23:26,156 --> 00:23:27,783
Instead,
no one told them.

652
00:23:27,866 --> 00:23:29,493
Two weeks later,
I'm in here.

653
00:23:30,327 --> 00:23:31,828
And I've been here
ever since.

654
00:23:32,662 --> 00:23:34,539
Is there anything else
I need to know?

655
00:23:36,958 --> 00:23:38,835
Then I need to find
Maria Gomez.

656
00:23:47,511 --> 00:23:49,763
Look, man, please,
I really don't
want to talk.

657
00:23:49,846 --> 00:23:51,014
Good,

658
00:23:51,098 --> 00:23:52,390
'cause I just want
you to listen.

659
00:23:56,019 --> 00:23:57,354
When I was a kid,

660
00:23:58,146 --> 00:23:59,606
I thought we had it good.

661
00:24:00,690 --> 00:24:02,025
And we did.
Had a nice house,

662
00:24:02,109 --> 00:24:03,276
nice neighborhood

663
00:24:03,360 --> 00:24:04,945
except for one thing.

664
00:24:06,446 --> 00:24:08,198
Turns out my father

665
00:24:09,658 --> 00:24:10,992
was a criminal.

666
00:24:11,284 --> 00:24:13,078
One day, he got caught,
he went to prison,

667
00:24:13,161 --> 00:24:14,871
and my whole life
fell apart.

668
00:24:15,622 --> 00:24:17,040
How old were you?

669
00:24:18,083 --> 00:24:19,334
Fifteen.

670
00:24:20,836 --> 00:24:22,504
Let me tell you something.

671
00:24:22,587 --> 00:24:24,965
I hated that man for doing
what he did to me.

672
00:24:25,715 --> 00:24:28,218
So, I did what messed up
15-year-olds do.

673
00:24:29,219 --> 00:24:30,595
You started acting out.

674
00:24:30,887 --> 00:24:32,222
Acting out?

675
00:24:32,806 --> 00:24:36,143
Brother, I was on my way
to a place worse than this.

676
00:24:38,103 --> 00:24:40,230
Finally, my mom
made me see someone.

677
00:24:40,564 --> 00:24:42,524
And he helped me realize

678
00:24:42,899 --> 00:24:45,443
that if I didn't change,
I was gonna ruin my life.

679
00:24:46,570 --> 00:24:49,072
So, I straightened out
and turned my life around.

680
00:24:49,614 --> 00:24:51,449
And that's why you do
what you do.

681
00:24:51,533 --> 00:24:52,617
Yeah.

682
00:24:55,162 --> 00:24:56,663
Why are you
telling me this?

683
00:24:56,746 --> 00:24:58,415
Because the way that man
got through to me

684
00:24:58,498 --> 00:25:00,417
was to open up
about himself.

685
00:25:01,084 --> 00:25:03,461
And I realize
that if I really want
to help you,

686
00:25:04,546 --> 00:25:06,131
I gotta do the same.

687
00:25:14,014 --> 00:25:15,849
All right, I dragged this out
as long as I can,

688
00:25:15,932 --> 00:25:17,601
but I'm pretty much done
drafting this motion,

689
00:25:17,684 --> 00:25:18,685
so I'll need you
to proof it, then...

690
00:25:18,768 --> 00:25:20,145
Harvey, before I do that,

691
00:25:20,228 --> 00:25:21,563
I think you should
take a look at these.

692
00:25:21,646 --> 00:25:23,523
What is it?
Cahill issued subpoenas

693
00:25:23,607 --> 00:25:25,984
to deposition
William Sutter
and Kevin Miller.

694
00:25:26,067 --> 00:25:27,694
That sneaky
son of a bitch.

695
00:25:27,777 --> 00:25:28,778
Why are you smiling?

696
00:25:28,862 --> 00:25:30,322
Because last night
I went to Cahill

697
00:25:30,405 --> 00:25:32,240
and tried to give him
Sutter's trading program.

698
00:25:33,158 --> 00:25:34,201
You did what?

699
00:25:34,284 --> 00:25:35,952
It was the only way
I could see to stop the case

700
00:25:36,036 --> 00:25:38,246
from getting dismissed.
But he wouldn't take it.

701
00:25:38,622 --> 00:25:39,873
And this buys you time.

702
00:25:39,956 --> 00:25:42,292
It does if the judge waits
to rule on our motion

703
00:25:42,375 --> 00:25:44,336
until after Cahill conducts
these depositions.

704
00:25:45,212 --> 00:25:46,213
Harvey,
even if that works,

705
00:25:46,296 --> 00:25:47,380
what if Cahill
doesn't get enough

706
00:25:47,464 --> 00:25:49,049
from the depositions
to keep the case alive?

707
00:25:49,132 --> 00:25:51,134
Then Mike's chance
of getting out
of prison is gone.

708
00:25:51,218 --> 00:25:52,886
Which means Cahill's
not the only one

709
00:25:52,969 --> 00:25:55,680
that needs to use this
to try and get something.

710
00:25:58,808 --> 00:26:00,018
I have to admit,
Miss Zane,

711
00:26:00,101 --> 00:26:01,811
when you said
you were looking
into the Bailey case,

712
00:26:01,895 --> 00:26:03,146
my interest
was piqued.

713
00:26:03,230 --> 00:26:04,689
That was a long time ago.

714
00:26:04,898 --> 00:26:06,441
Well, you've obviously
come a long way

715
00:26:06,524 --> 00:26:07,776
since your public
defender days.

716
00:26:07,859 --> 00:26:09,236
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)
You don't exactly see

717
00:26:09,319 --> 00:26:11,238
the best of humanity
at that job,

718
00:26:11,321 --> 00:26:13,823
which makes it one
you can only do
for so long.

719
00:26:13,990 --> 00:26:16,284
But you didn't come here
to be my therapist.

720
00:26:16,368 --> 00:26:19,162
No, I came to talk
about Maria Gomez.

721
00:26:19,246 --> 00:26:20,247
What about her?

722
00:26:20,330 --> 00:26:21,998
I'm curious as to
how you can have

723
00:26:22,082 --> 00:26:23,458
an alibi witness
on a murder case

724
00:26:23,541 --> 00:26:25,377
and your client
ends up on death row.

725
00:26:25,460 --> 00:26:27,295
Because I didn't have
an alibi witness.

726
00:26:27,379 --> 00:26:29,256
I had a no-show
who vanished
into thin air

727
00:26:29,339 --> 00:26:31,132
and I didn't have
the resources
to find her.

728
00:26:31,216 --> 00:26:33,218
And you didn't think
to ask the police at trial

729
00:26:33,301 --> 00:26:35,262
why they didn't follow up
on Leonard's alibi?

730
00:26:35,345 --> 00:26:36,346
I did think of it,

731
